Privacy Policy
1. Introduction
We respect your privacy. This Policy explains what information Komi Warframe (“we,” “us”) collects, how we use it, and your choices.

2. Information We Collect
Automatically Collected Data:

Device identifiers (e.g., OS version, hardware model)

Usage data (e.g., session length, features used)

Crash reports and diagnostics

User-Provided Data:

If you contact us (e.g., via email or in-app feedback), you may provide your name and email address.

3. Use of Information
We use your data to:

Provide, operate, and improve the app.

Diagnose technical issues and crashes.

Analyze usage trends to enhance features.

Respond to your support requests.

4. Cookies and Tracking
If the app’s web-based features use cookies or similar technologies (e.g., localStorage), these help retain your preferences and track basic usage patterns. You may disable cookies in your browser, but some features may not function correctly.

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We will not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties, except:

Service Providers: to host or maintain our servers (under strict confidentiality).

Legal Requirements: if required by law or to protect our rights.

6. Data Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures (e.g., encryption in transit, secure servers) to protect your data. However, no method is 100% secure; use at your own risk.

7. International Transfers
Your data may be processed in countries other than your own. By using the app, you consent to such transfers under this Policy.

8. Children’s Privacy
We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you are under 13, do not use the app. If we learn we have collected data from a child under 13, we will delete it.

9. Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

Access, correct, or delete your personal data.

Object to or restrict processing.

Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.

To exercise these rights, contact us at the address below.

10. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy. We will notify you by posting the new Policy in the app or on our website. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.

11. Contact Us
If you have questions or wish to exercise your data-related rights, please email:
lawrenceb.dev@gmail.com
